Extra files: README (this file)
----------------------------------------------------
This is an assignment where we are creating a program to place N queens on an N X N board 
where no queens attack eachother. We are given a few queens already placed and must either find
a solution, or discover there there is No solution for the given input.
----------------------------------------------------
USAGE: 
1) Run "make", to get executable "main".
2) Run "./main <INPUT FILE> <OUTPUT FILE>"

Each line of INPUT FILE should have N as the first numeber, and then the (x,y) coordinates of each given queen.
Each corresponding line of OUTPUT FILE will be the (x,y) coordinates of each queen on the 
board once solved, or "No solution".
